{"key":"processedPost-19541744","value":{"id":19541744,"first":19511982,"last":24817404,"when":1391919723,"utime":"02/09/14 06:22 AM","content":"Dude, the hydro nutes are not for mushrooms any more than a T-bone steak is for plants.&nbsp; Whether the straw colonizes or not is irrelevant.&nbsp; Mycelium will colonize straw with all sorts of stuff on it.<br />Minerals <i>are</i> nutrients for fungi.&nbsp; Fungi were around for about a billion years or so before plants developed.&nbsp; Mycelium does not colonize and feed off plastic.&nbsp; Mycelium does colonize and feed off vermiculite, as anyone who does brf cakes can attest.&nbsp; The cakes will shrink to ten percent or so of their original size after several flushes.<br />When mycelium crawls up a jar or plastic bag above the substrate, that is not colonization.<br />RR","title":"Re: Hydroponic Nutrient Experiment Straw & LC"}}